cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 

1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - This paper primarily focuses on the topology of the Autonomous Systems graph of the Internet, which is a key area of research in networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the evolution of the Internet topology over time, which can be seen as a social network of interconnected autonomous systems. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper analyzes the changes in the Internet topology over time and hypothesizes that these changes are due to changes in peering policies, which can be seen as a control problem. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper discusses the evolution of the Internet topology over time, which has implications for network security and cryptography. 
5. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper analyzes the changes in the Internet topology over time and evaluates different models of the Internet graph, which can be seen as an information theory problem.
